@spec vm_reswing_lane_stability_spec  src=tests/specs/vm_reswing_lane_stability_spec.lua  loc=71  sha=d415ad4  cases=1
@exercises trackerView (h.vm), trackerManager (h.tm), midiManager (h.fm)
@surface   vm:setGridSize, tm:markSwingStale, tm:rebuild, fm:dump
@harness   mk{seed.notes}

# Intent
  L2 lane stability under reswing's rounding edge.
  
  The audit (design/audit/L2_lane_stability.md) found that reswing's
  monotone-but-rounded `swing.fromLogical` can push diff-pitch
  col-mates sitting near `lenient` overlap past the threshold, after
  which `allocateNoteColumn` rejects the persisted lane and the
  successor drifts to a fresh lane. The fix is `conformOverlaps`
  (vm), which clips the predecessor's tail back to threshold before
  the writes commit.

# Cases
  @case 'diff-pitch col-mates at lenient overlap survive a reswing into c58 in lane 1'  [harness]  @ 18-68

# Uses (outbound edges)
  @use call vm:setGridSize  @ 48
  @use call tm:markSwingStale  @ 49
  @use call tm:rebuild  @ 49
  @use call fm:dump  @ 51
